    Lavage_de_trains_title: "trains washing",
    Lavage_de_trains_small_description: "Train Washing Machine is a fixed installation in terms of the main structure and they are designed for washing trains, high-speed trains, locomotives and underground trains by passing vehicles at constant speed or moving washing devices on the stationary vehicle.",
    Lavage_de_trains_large_description:"With the RBH brand, we establish automatic train washing facilities that meet many different needs \n\n The Train Washing Machine is a fixed installation in terms of the main structure and they are designed for washing trains, high-speed trains, locomotives and underground trains by passing vehicles at constant speed or moving washing devices on the stationary vehicle.\nIn our installations, the wagons can be passed through the washing units with their own traction with operator driving control, and efficient washing can be achieved by moving them at low fixed or variable speed thanks to our towing systems specials for wagons.\nTo operate the system, we install PLC computerized and SCADA controlled systems. In addition, the camera control system can be installed internally at the installation site. Train washing and drying systems consist of different units. These units are placed in the installation according to their functions and are automatically activated according to the washing order.\n\nWE HAVE INSTALLED PRE-WATER, DETERGENT, SHAMPOO, WAX BELTS These are units formed by placing nozzles along one or two lines that will create a curtain of water at certain pressures and flow rates at certain intervals to wash the entire surface of the vehicle. When passing through the car wash belt, water will be sprayed onto the vehicle and the spraying process will stop when the vehicle has finished passing.\nIn the polishing process, the entire surface of the washed vehicle is sprayed intensively with the lacquer chemical which helps in drying at a certain rate. The lacquer also prevents water from sticking to the surface before it dries. It is mounted on the construction in the form of arcs. The amount of dosing on the line can be adjusted with the dosing pump.\nTrain washing systems are fixed installations through which the vehicle passes at constant speed or the movement of washing devices above the stationary vehicle; They are designed for washing trains, locomotives, wagons, subways, trams, etc. A horizontal brush, top corner brushes with a 45 degree angle, top brush, side brush and pressure washing belt, emollient (dirt softening) belt, washing and drying unit of the chassis can be added to our models as an option.",

